  "doc_id": null,
  "text": "Setting up an XMT scan can be viewed as an optimization problem between voxel size, noise level, scan duration, and radiation dose to the sample. In this work, the magnification, exposure time and number of projections were varied in order to find the best configuration for imaging live plants, i.e. the shortest scan time that still results in reconstructions of acceptable quality. We will summarize the key points to be considered when selecting these parameters as they apply to the system used in this study. For a comprehensive discussion, the reader is referred to e.g. the introductory text by S.R. Stock [CITATION_1] .",
